---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Red Orange Yellow Green Blue View
description: a read-only display of a five-level colour status
---

{% from "components/red-orange-yellow-green-blue-view/macro.njk" import redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView %}

<h2>Each status level</h2>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "red" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "orange" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "yellow" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "green" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "blue" }) }}</p>

<h2>Unknown status</h2>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({}) }}</p>

<h2>Custom text</h2>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "red", text: "Critical" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "orange", text: "High priority" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "yellow", text: "Caution" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "green", text: "On track" }) }}</p>
<p>{{ redOrangeYellowGreenBlueView({ status: "blue", text: "Informational" }) }}</p>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>Colour alone is never sufficient. The indicator dot is
  <code>aria-hidden</code> while the visible label (e.g. "Red")
  is read by assistive technology.</p>
